properties.Name: LifeInsuranceProvision
properties.Description:
A specific term or condition contained in the policy clause of an Insurance Policy.

Ex:
- Waiver of Premium, a provision of a Life Insurance Policy which continues coverage if the insured becomes totally disabled without further premium payments.

Columns.Name: InsuranceProvisionId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Insurance Provision.

Columns.Name: InsuranceProvisionName
Columns.Description: The name of an Insurance Provision.

Columns.Name: InsuranceProvisionDescription
Columns.Description: The description of an Insurance Provision.

Columns.Name: InsuranceProvisionTermsConditionsText
Columns.Description: The specific terms or conditions text of the Insurance Provision.

Columns.Name: InsuranceProvisionExclusionsRestrictions
Columns.Description: Any exclusions or restrictions that further define the associated Insurance Provision.

Columns.Name: LifeInsuranceProvisionTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Insurance Provision Type.
